    description: {
      en: 'Rules-owner clarification (2026-06-20, IG Cavalry Regiment Q5): this restriction should hard-block selection (greyed out + tooltip), not just be informational text. Implemented v0.96 via ArchetypeRule.lowMoveMustEmbark + engine/transportGate.ts, wired into SlotPanel.tsx\'s catalog (disabled button + title tooltip when Movement<12" and unit_type !== "Infantry"). Enabled for IG Cavalry Regiment/Mechanised Company, SM/GSC/Votann/Orks (all via fastArchetype). FIXED: re-checked the remaining 4 factions against their own digests — Adeptus Custodes\' "Kataphraktoi" has the exact same M<12"-conditional wording (confirmed in rules-model/adeptus_custodes.md) and was missing the flag despite already having the matching notes text; now wired. Eldar\'s "Windhost" already used fastArchetype and had the gate enabled all along. Sororitas\' "Holy Vanguard" (all Dominion models must embark, unconditionally) and Tyranids\' "Tyrannocyte Assault" (all units, unconditionally — dropPodArchetype) turned out to be a different rule shape entirely — mandatory embark regardless of Movement, not an M<12" selection gate — so they correctly do not use this field; nothing left to enable there.',
      de: 'Klarstellung des Regelinhabers (2026-06-20, IG Cavalry Regiment F5): diese Einschränkung sollte die Auswahl hart blockieren. Implementiert über ArchetypeRule.lowMoveMustEmbark. BEHOBEN: Adeptus Custodes\' "Kataphraktoi" hatte den exakt gleichen Wortlaut, aber das Flag fehlte — jetzt verdrahtet. Eldars "Windhost" hatte es bereits. Sororitas\' "Holy Vanguard" und Tyranids\' "Tyrannocyte Assault" sind eine andere Regel (bedingungslose Einbettung, kein M<12"-Gate) — korrekt unverändert.',
      es: 'Aclaración del dueño de las reglas (2026-06-20, IG Cavalry Regiment P5): esta restricción debería bloquear la selección por completo. Implementado vía ArchetypeRule.lowMoveMustEmbark. ARREGLADO: "Kataphraktoi" de Adeptus Custodes tenía el mismo texto exacto pero le faltaba el flag — ya conectado. "Windhost" de Eldar ya lo tenía. "Holy Vanguard" de Sororitas y "Tyrannocyte Assault" de Tyranids resultaron ser una regla distinta (embarque incondicional, no un gate por M<12") — correctamente sin cambios.',
    },
