    description: 'Found 2026-06-19 via live builder exploration: "Familiar" (general.json, "Only for Sorcerers.") was purchasable (+5 pts, not greyed out) on a base Daemon Prince that has not taken the optional Psyker upgrade. Re-confirmed 2026-06-21 against `Chaos Space Marines ENG.ods` "Armory": 4 such text-only restrictions exist with no `requires_keywords` — Familiar ("Only for Sorcerers"), Cursed blade ("Only for Lieutenants"), Chaos Space Marine bike ("Infantry only"), Terminator armor ("Only for infantry") — vs. the already-working Demagogue ("Only for Dark Apostles", requires_keywords:["Priest"]). FIXED: added requires_keywords to all 4 — ["Lieutenant"] and ["Infantry"] x2 were already derivable (keywords.ts\'s ROLE_KW_FROM_NAME already maps /lieutenant/i and unit_type already contributes "Infantry"), no engine change needed for those. Familiar needed a NEW distinct \'Sorcerer\' role keyword (not the existing /sorcerer/i→\'Psyker\' mapping) since 4 OTHER CSM units are also is_psyker:true (Tzaangor Shaman, Rubric Marines, Scarab Occult Terminators, Dark Commune) but are not Sorcerers — reusing \'Psyker\' would have wrongly opened Familiar to all of them. Follow-up 2026-06-21 (user-confirmed): Rubric Marines\' "Aspiring Sorcerer" and Scarab Occult Terminators\' "Scarab Occult Sorcerer" ARE meant to qualify too — both units have `champion_has_armory: true` / `has_armory_access: false`, meaning the champion (always a Sorcerer by name) is the ONLY model that can ever buy Armory items in that unit. Added an explicit "Sorcerer" entry to both units\' `keywords[]` (data-level, not a new name-regex, since their unit name doesn\'t contain "sorcerer"). Dark Commune\'s "Mindsorcerer" does NOT qualify and needed no change: `has_armory_access: false` AND `champion_has_armory: false` — the whole unit has no Armory access at all, so Familiar was never reachable there regardless of keyword. Tzaangor Shaman (also is_psyker:true, has_armory_access:true) correctly stays excluded — it has no "Sorcerer" role text or keyword, matching the literal "Only for Sorcerers" (not "Only for Psykers") canon wording.',
