    description: 'Reported by the user (2026-06-20) via a points mismatch under Plaguehost: a Chaos Rhino with no options bought showed only the optional Havoc launcher, not its default Combi-bolter — even though Plaguehost\'s mandatory Combi-bolter→Poison(4+) surcharge (+2pts, ods-verbatim) was still being charged correctly, so the cost (111 base + 10 forced Mark of Nurgle + 2 mandatory upgrade = 123) was right but the displayed weapon list was wrong. Root cause: `resolver.ts`\'s `computeWeaponsToShow` builds an "optional weapon" map by matching option-group CHOICE names against weapon names — Chaos Rhino\'s "May be equipped with one of the following: Combi-flamer/Combi-bolter/Combi-melta" group (an ADDITIVE second-mount option, no `replaces` link, ods-verbatim "+8/+11/+18") has a choice literally named "Combi-bolter", same name as the unit\'s own default/free weapon from `equipped_with` — so the heuristic treated the default copy as "hidden until bought" too. Fixed by skipping a weapon from the optional-map when its name is already present in `unit.equipped_with` (it\'s guaranteed regardless of the option), and by skipping `replaces`-bearing groups entirely from this heuristic (they already have their own dedicated swap-counting path further down the same function).',
