    description: 'Found while investigating the Blightlord Terminators / Chaos Rhino reports above (2026-06-20/21). Once `computeWeaponsToShow` was fixed to stop hiding default weapons that share a name with an unrelated additive option (see the Chaos Rhino fix), a full codebase audit was run for the INVERSE problem: option groups whose `header` clearly describes a replacement swap ("may swap their X for Y", "may exchange X for") but whose `replaces` field was missing/empty, with no choice name matching X either — meaning the engine had no way to infer the swap and just kept showing both weapons. Confirmed live by the user on Blightlord Terminators (Balesword + Bubonic axe + Power fist all shown at once for a 5-model unit that should only ever show one melee weapon type per model). A sub-agent audit found 202 header matches; 87 were fixed with a verified `replaces: [...]` cross-checked against that unit\'s own `equipped_with`/`weapons[]` text (Space Marines 19, Tau Empire 12, Tyranids 12, Chaos Space Marines 9, Dark Eldar 7, Leagues of Votann 6, Imperial Guard 5, Harlequins 5, Grey Knights 5, Orks 4, Adeptus Sororitas/Inquisition/Necrons 1 each). Points were never affected by this bug — option prices were always charged correctly; only the displayed weapon list was wrong. The remaining ~115 of the original 202 candidates were either false positives (vaguer header phrasing that does not actually need a replaces — the regex over-matched) or genuinely ambiguous/missing source data, logged below as 8 specific skipped cases for manual follow-up: `dark_eldar/talos.ts` (2 Macro-scalpel slots, ambiguous which group targets which), `tyranids/carnifex_brood.ts` (2 Monstrous scything talon slots, same ambiguity), `grey_knights/paladin_squad.ts` ("Nemesis falchions" not present anywhere in weapons[]), `imperial_guard/bullgryns.ts` (Brute/Plate shield are armor, not weapons-pipeline items), `imperial_guard/tauros.ts` (Tauros grenade launcher missing from weapons[] entirely — separate pre-existing gap), `space_marines/deathwing_knights.ts` + `tau_empire/barracuda_air_superiority_fighter.ts` (both fell outside the audit\'s regex pattern, not yet scanned).',
